verbose_text: Next, the present study investigated the protein expression levels of RhoA and ROCK1 at 24 and 48 h after sepsis (XREF_FIG), and the results revealed that rhNRG-1 is able to suppress the expression of RhoA and ROCK1 in vivo and in vitro, indicating that NRG-1 functioned in the regulation of the anti-inflammatory and anti-oxidative stress action, which is based on the RhoA / ROCK pathway.
